-- slice E1b: a top-level VALUE binding referenced from a FUNCTION (not just main).
-- `base` lives in a module global `@mdk_g_base` (init'd in the @main prologue);
-- `addBase`, a sibling `define`, loads it — the gap #7 fix (a value binding
-- referenced from another function is no longer an unbound local).
base = 100
addBase x = x + base
main = addBase 5
